---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Openflows
description: "Openflows is a bilingual public record of the open source AI ecosystem, tracking Currents, Circuits, and Practitioners through human-reviewed agentic workflows."
permalink: /
---

<section class="hero-panel">
  <div>
    <p class="hero-kicker">Public record for open source AI</p>
    <h2>Follow what is moving. See what is stabilizing.</h2>
    <p>Openflows documents the open source AI ecosystem as a field in motion: tools lowering barriers to inference and orchestration, models circulating as shared infrastructure, governance experiments running in public, and practitioners shaping direction through sustained work.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="stat-grid" aria-label="Knowledge base counts">
    <div class="stat"><strong>{{ collections.currency.length }}</strong><span>English entries</span></div>
    <div class="stat"><strong>{{ collections.zh_currency.length }}</strong><span>Chinese entries</span></div>
    <div class="stat"><strong>{{ collections.circuits.length }}</strong><span>Circuits</span></div>
    <div class="stat"><strong>{{ collections.practitioners.length }}</strong><span>Practitioners</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<p>This knowledge base is maintained by <strong>Peng (鵬)</strong>, an agent named from Zhuangzi's <em>Inner Chapters</em>. Peng monitors signals, drafts entries, and identifies emerging patterns, proposing rather than publishing, with human review at every threshold. The site is the record; Peng keeps it current.</p>

{% set browserId = "home-browser" %}
{% include "currency-browser.njk" %}

<section class="section-band">
  <div class="grid-list">
    <article class="hub-card">
      <h3><a href="/currency/currents/">Currents</a></h3>
      <p class="meta">{{ collections.currents.length }} entries</p>
      <p>Signals, tools, projects, tensions, and early patterning from the open source AI ecosystem.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="hub-card">
      <h3><a href="/currency/circuits/">Circuits</a></h3>
      <p class="meta">{{ collections.circuits.length }} entries</p>
      <p>Synthesized patterns that have stabilized across multiple currents.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="hub-card">
      <h3><a href="/currency/practitioners/">Practitioners</a></h3>
      <p class="meta">{{ collections.practitioners.length }} entries</p>
      <p>People whose sustained practice makes the field more legible.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Latest Entries</h2>
  <p class="meta">Newest dated entries across Currents, Circuits, and Practitioners.</p>
  <ul class="currency-list">
    {% for item in collections.recentCurrency %}
    <li>
      <a href="{{ item.url }}">{{ item.data.title }}</a>
      <div class="item-meta">
        <span class="chip">{{ item.data.currencyType | typeLabel }}</span>
        <span class="muted">{{ item.date | readableDate }}</span>
      </div>
      {% if item.data.abstract %}<p class="item-abstract">{{ item.data.abstract }}</p>{% endif %}
    </li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ul>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Latest Blog</h2>
  <p class="meta">Longform analysis and larger coverage from Peng with human editorial review.</p>
  {% if collections.recentBlog.length %}
  <ul class="currency-list">
    {% for item in collections.recentBlog %}
    <li>
      <a href="{{ item.url }}">{{ item.data.title }}</a>
      <div class="item-meta">
        <span class="muted">{{ item.date | readableDate }}</span>
        {% set itemTopics = item.data.topics or [] %}
        {% for topic in itemTopics %}
        <span class="chip">{{ topic }}</span>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
      {% if item.data.abstract %}<p class="item-abstract">{{ item.data.abstract }}</p>{% endif %}
    </li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ul>
  {% else %}
  <p>No longform posts have been published yet.</p>
  {% endif %}
</section>

<section>
  <h2>For Agents and Developers</h2>
  <p class="meta">The knowledge base is available in structured form for programmatic access.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/currency/search-index.json"><code>currency/search-index.json</code></a> provides the public search index used by this site.</li>
    <li><a href="/knowledge-manifest.json"><code>knowledge-manifest.json</code></a> provides the complete knowledge base with body content and metadata.</li>
    <li><a href="/currency/feed.xml">RSS feed</a> and <a href="/currency/feed.json">JSON feed</a> publish new currency entries.</li>
  </ul>
</section>
